 The National and State House of Assembly Election Tribunal sitting in Kaduna state, on Saturday orders for a re-run in 22 polling units of Kagarko State Assembly Constituency. The order followed the Tribunal verdict sacking Mr Morondia Tanko, candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the March 9 election for Kagarko State Constituency who was declared winner of the poll. Mr Nuhu Shadalafiya former deputy Speaker of the State Assembly and candidate of the All Progressive Congress (APC) had challenged the victory of Tanko and PDP for Kagarko State Constituency at the Tribunal. Continue reading Tribunal sacks Kaduna lawmaker, orders for re-run in 22 polling units at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard